'''João Pedro Gonçalves Neves''' ({{IPA|pt|ʒuˈɐ̃w̃ˈnɛvɨʃ}}; born 27 September 2004) is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]]. Primarily a [[Central Midfielder|central midfielder]], Neves is also able to play as a [[defensive midfielder]] and occasionally a [[right-back]]. Known for his elite defensive work rate, composure, and vision, he is regarded as one of the best young players in the world.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Swan |first=Rob |last2=Malyan |first2=Christy |last3=Murray |first3=Will |last4=Hepburn |first4=Daniel |date=10 November 2023 |title=The 25 best footballers in the world right now - ranked in order |url=https://www.givemesport.com/best-football-players-in-the-world/ |access-date=5 August 2025 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=O'Brien |first=Sean |date=1 November 2025 |title=Top 10 young players in world as Arsenal starlet Max Dowman tipped to join list |url=https://talksport.com/football/3052953/lamine-yamal-best-young-players-max-dowman/ |access-date=14 March 2026 |website=talkSPORT |language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Swan |first=Rob |last2=Ritchie |first2=Calum |date=30 June 2022 |title=The 25 Best Young Players in World Football (Ranked) |url=https://www.givemesport.com/best-young-players-in-world-football-soccer-ranked/ |access-date=14 March 2026 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref>

Coming through [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]'s youth system, Neves impressed during his time with [[S.L. Benfica B|the reserve side]], winning the [[UEFA Youth League]] in [[2021–22 UEFA Youth League|2021–22]], being instrumental part of Benfica's first European trophy in 60 years. He was subsequently promoted to the first-team, making his professional debut at age 18, where he helped Benfica win the [[2022–23 Primeira Liga|league title]] in [[2022–23 S.L. Benfica season|his first season]] with the side. In August 2024, Neves joined Paris Saint-Germain for a transfer fee of €60 million, being a prominent player as the club won their first [[UEFA Champions League]] titles back-to-back in [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|2025]] and [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|2026]], with the former being part of a [[continental treble]]. 

Neves is a former [[Portugal national youth football team|Portugal youth international]], representing his country at various levels. He made his senior international debut in 2023, representing Portugal at the [[UEFA Euro 2024]]. He also won the [[UEFA Nations League]] in [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|2025]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Tavira]], Neves began his youth career with hometown club Casa Benfica Tavira, one of [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]'s feeder clubs, he then spent four seasons in Benfica's development centre in Algarve, before moving to Benfica's [[S.L. Benfica (youth)|main academy]] in 2016.<ref name=contract>{{cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/futebol/plantel-principal/joao-neves|title=João Neves profile|date=28 November 2021|accessdate=26 April 2022|website=record.pt|language=Portuguese}}</ref> Neves signed his first professional contract with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in December 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2020/12/11/futebol-formacao-benfica-joao-neves-assina-contrato-profissional|title=João Neves assina contrato profissional|trans-title=João Neves signs professional contract|date=11 December 2020|accessdate=15 August 2022|website=slbenfica.pt|language=Portuguese}}</ref>

===Benfica===
====2022–23: Early career and first-team breakthrough====
[[File:João Neves, SLB - Entrevista 2023-03-23.png|thumb|upright|left|Neves with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2023]]
Neves was a part of the Benfica U19 team which topped their [[2021–22 UEFA Youth League]] [[2021–22 UEFA Youth League group stage#Group E|group]] against [[YFS Dynamo Kyiv of Valeriy Lobanovsky|Dynamo Kyiv]], [[FC Barcelona (youth)|Barcelona]] and [[FC Bayern Munich Junior Team|Bayern Munich]],<ref>{{Cite web|date=20 October 2021|title=Youth League: Benfica-Bayern|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/emdirecto/liga-campeoes/direto-youth-league-benfica-bayern-14237555.html|access-date=25 January 2022|website=[[O Jogo]]|language=pt-PT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=20 October 2021|title=Categórico escreveu-se com golos|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2021/10/20/futebol-uefa-youth-league-jogo-benfica-bayern-3-jornada-grupo-e|access-date=25 January 2022|website=SL Benfica|language=pt}}</ref> and eventually won the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/amp/benfica/youth-league/benfica-a-historia-dos-24-jogadores-que-venceram-a-youth-league|title=Benfica: a história dos 24 jogadores que venceram a Youth League|website=maisfutebol.iol.pt|access-date=29 August 2022|archive-date=26 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221026082110/https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/amp/benfica/youth-league/benfica-a-historia-dos-24-jogadores-que-venceram-a-youth-league|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Benfica B in a 1–1 LigaPro draw to [[Académico de Viseu F.C.|Académico de Viseu]] on 6 August 2022.<ref name="contract" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=João Neves signs new contract |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2023/08/11/futebol-benfica-joao-neves-assinatura-de-novo-contrato |access-date=2024-02-26 |website=www.slbenfica.pt |language=en}}</ref> On 24 August, Neves started in Benfica's 1–0 against [[Peñarol]] at the [[2022 Under-20 Intercontinental Cup]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://observador.pt/2022/08/21/entrou-marcou-decidiu-benfica-vence-penarol-no-mitico-centenario-com-golo-de-luis-semedo-e-conquista-taca-intercontinental-sub-20/ | title=Entrou, marcou, decidiu: Benfica vence Peñarol no mítico Centenário com golo de Luís Semedo e conquista Taça Intercontinental Sub-20 | language=pt | work=Observador | first=Bruno | last=Roseiro | date=21 August 2022 | accessdate=23 August 2025 }}</ref>

During the league break to facilitate the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], he made his unofficial debut for Benfica's first team on 11 December 2022, in a closed-doors friendly against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Benfica-Sevilha, 0-1: os destaques das águias |url=https://cnnportugal.iol.pt/benfica/sevilha/benfica-sevilha-0-1-os-destaques-das-aguias |access-date=26 February 2024 |website=CNN Portugal |language=pt}}</ref> During this time, Benfica's first team manager [[Roger Schmidt (footballer)|Roger Schmidt]] invited him to participate in several first-team training sessions, impressing him with his ability, dedication and maturity on the ball. On 21 December, Neves signed a contract extension with Benfica until 2028.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Benfica anuncia renovação com João Neves |url=https://cnnportugal.iol.pt/benfica/joao-neves/benfica-anuncia-renovacao-com-joao-neves |access-date=26 February 2024 |website=CNN Portugal |language=pt}}</ref> He made his debut for the senior team on the first day of 2023, coming on late as a substitute in the 3–0 defeat to [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] in the [[Primeira Liga]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=João Neves: "Passados dez anos de muito esforço, alcancei o meu sonho" |url=https://cnnportugal.iol.pt/benfica/joao-neves/joao-neves-passados-dez-anos-de-muito-esforco-alcancei-o-meu-sonho |access-date=26 February 2024 |website=CNN Portugal |language=pt}}</ref> On 7 March, Neves made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut, replacing [[João Mário (footballer, born January 1993)|João Mário]] in the 74th minute and providing an assist on Benfica's fifth goal, in their 5–1 home win against [[Club Brugge]] in the second leg of the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League#Round of 16|Champions League round-of-16]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Abola.pt |date=7 March 2023 |title=Benfica "Especial é jogar com a camisola do Benfica" {{!}} Abola.pt |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/especial-e-jogar-com-a-camisola-do-benfica-2023080900570662876 |access-date=26 February 2024 |website=Abola.pt |language=pt}}</ref>

In the final months of the season, following the departure of [[Enzo Fernández]], Neves eventually earned a place in the starting eleven over [[Florentino Luís]], most notably scoring his first goal for the club on 21 May against [[Lisbon derby|crosstown rivals]] [[Sporting CP]] in the ''[[Lisbon derby]]'', securing his side a draw after they were down by two goals at half-time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/sporting-benfica-joao-neves-arrancou-empate-ao-cair-do-pano-16396205.html|title=Sporting-Benfica: João Neves arrancou empate ao cair do pano|publisher=[[O Jogo]]|date=21 May 2023|access-date=17 September 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=VÍDEO: João Neves, aos 90+4, dá empate ao Benfica em Alvalade |url=https://cnnportugal.iol.pt/liga/videos-liga/video-joao-neves-aos-90-4-da-empate-ao-benfica-em-alvalade |access-date=26 February 2024 |website=CNN Portugal |language=pt}}</ref> He would make 17 league appearances for Benfica as they sealed their first league title in four years, following a 3–0 home win over [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]], on the final day of the league campaign.<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 May 2023 |title=The justice of those who became champions early on! |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2023/05/27/futebol-benfica-cronica-jogo-santa-clara-34-jornada-liga-bwin |access-date=26 February 2024 |website=www.slbenfica.pt |language=en}}</ref>

====2023–24: Primeira Liga Team of Year and departure====
Neves started the [[2023–24 S.L. Benfica season|2023–24 season]], on 9 August, being named man of the match in the 2–0 victory over [[FC Porto|Porto]] in the [[2023 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira|Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/id/berita/angel-di-maria-and-petar-musa-on-target-as-benfica-beat-porto-2-0-in-the-super-cup-38006246 |title=Ángel Di María and Petar Musa on target as Benfica beat Porto 2-0 in the Super Cup |publisher=OneFootball |date=9 August 2023 }}</ref> On 12 November, Neves scored the 94th minute equalizer in an eventual 2–1 league victory over rivals Sporting CP, at the [[Estádio da Luz]];<ref>{{Cite web |last=Roseiro |first=Bruno |date=12 November 2023 |title=João Neves, um gigante dois em um que vê soluções e esconde problemas (a crónica do Benfica-Sporting) |trans-title=João Neves, a two-for-one giant that sees solutions and hides problems (Benfica-Sporting chronicle) |url=https://observador.pt/2023/11/12/joao-neves-um-gigante-dois-em-um-que-ve-solucoes-e-esconde-problemas-a-cronica-do-benfica-sporting/ |access-date=13 November 2023 |website=Observador |language=pt-PT}}</ref> while also receiving the [[Player of the match|Man of the Match]] award.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 November 2023 |title=João Neves eleito "Homem do Jogo" no dérbi, mas houve outros destaques |trans-title=João Neves chosen as "Man of the Match" in the derby, but there were other highlights |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/joao-neves-eleito-homem-do-jogo-no-derbi-mas-houve-outros-destaques-35485049 |access-date=13 November 2023 |website=OneFootball |language=pt-pt}}</ref> Over the following months, Neves established himself as one of the best midfielders in Portugal, being voted as the Primeira Liga's Midfielder of the Month between the months September and December, a feat which he repeated in February and March 2024, with only Braga's [[Rodrigo Zalazar]] winning it in January.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/joao-neves-benficas-homegrown-superstar-in-midfield/|title=João Neves: Benfica's Homegrown Superstar in Midfield|publisher=Breaking the Lines |date=29 March 2024}}</ref> At the end of the season, despite Benfica finishing as runners-up in the league, Neves was named in the [[2023–24 Primeira Liga#Annual awards|Team of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/jota-silva-fecha-o-onze-do-ano-da-primeira-liga|title=Jota Silva fecha o 'Onze do Ano' da Primeira Liga|trans-title=Jota Silva completes the First League's 'All-Star Team'|publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]]|language=pt|date=13 June 2024|access-date=31 October 2024}}</ref>

In July 2024, it was reported that [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG) had made an initial bid for Neves of €70 million (£59 million).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/trouble-man-utd-psg-outbid-red-devils-eur70m-offe-benfica-joao-neves/blt88849848bd9f0f82#cs55a67f8cb17a4502/|title=Trouble for Man Utd as PSG outbid Red Devils with €70m offer for Benfica star Joao Neves|publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=11 July 2024}}</ref> Their offer was reportedly rejected and negotiations continued, with Benfica being adamant that he would not be sold for less than his €120 million release clause, despite PSG agreeing personal terms with Neves.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2024/agreement-reached-in-principle-between-psg-and-joao-neves/|title=AGREEMENT REACHED IN PRINCIPLE BETWEEN PSG AND JOÃO NEVES|publisher=Get French Football News|date=16 July 2024}}</ref> Shortly after, Benfica's President [[Rui Costa]] denied that he "would only leave for his release clause and therefore, those claims were false", but confirmed the club had received a bid for him, with negotiations between them and a club still proceeding.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/benfica-arsenal-man-utd-psg-target-joao-neves-eur120m-release-clause/blt5a89b9348c072215#csfcc13df1fa12b61e|title=Benfica confirm they have received bid for Arsenal, Man Utd & PSG target Joao Neves as club president hints they may accept bid lower than €120m release clause|publisher=Goal|date=20 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/rui-costa-sobre-joao-neves-ha-uma-proposta-em-cima-da-mesa-que-esta-a-ser-avaliada-2024072014535828656|title=Rui Costa sobre João Neves: "Há uma proposta em cima da mesa que está a ser avaliada"|publisher=ABola|date=20 July 2024}}</ref> On 2 August, Rui Costa confirmed Neves' departure to Paris Saint-Germain, stating that he could not refuse a €70 million offer for him, leading Benfica to confirm his transfer three days later.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/5117742663/rui-costa-justifica-saida-de-joao-neves-verbas-de-70-milhoes-sao-impossiveis-de-abdicar/|title=Rui Costa justifica saída de João Neves: "Verbas de 70 milhões são impossíveis de abdicar"|trans-title=Rui Costa justifies João Neves' departure: "Funds of 70 million are impossible to refuse"|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|language=pt|date=2 August 2024|access-date=5 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/benfica-presta-esclarecimento-sobre-joao-neves-2024080507005190837|title=Benfica presta esclarecimento sobre João Neves|trans-title=Benfica provides clarification on João Neves|newspaper=[[A Bola]]|language=pt|date=5 August 2024|access-date=5 August 2024}}</ref>

=== Paris Saint-Germain ===
On 5 August 2024, Neves signed a five-year contract with Paris Saint-Germain, for a €59.9 million fee plus €10 million in potential add-ons,<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=5 August 2024 |title=João Neves deixa o Benfica para rumar ao Paris Saint-Germain por 59,9 ME |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-internacional/joao-neves-deixa-o-benfica-para-rumar-ao-paris-saint-germain-por-599-me_d1591058 |access-date=24 August 2024 |website=RTP Desporto |language=pt}}</ref> and [[Renato Sanches]] moving in the other direction on a loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pt.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-principal/content/o-paris-saint-germain-assina-com-o-meia-portugues-joao-neves-psg-news-mercato-2425|title=Paris Saint-Germain signs Portuguese midfielder João Neves|publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|date=5 August 2024|access-date=5 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5681394/2024/08/05/joao-neves-psg-transfer/|title=PSG confirm Joao Neves signing on five-year contract|publisher=[[The Athletic]]|date=5 August 2024|access-date=5 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/2608251/sai-joao-neves-entra-renato-sanches-os-detalhes-do-acordo-benfica-psg|title=Sai João Neves, entra Renato Sanches. Os detalhes do acordo Benfica-PSG|publisher=Desporto ao Minuto|date=1 August 2024|access-date=5 August 2024}}</ref>

[[File:Neves asse psg 2425.png|thumb|upright|Neves playing for [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] during the 2024–25 season]]
On 16 August, Neves made his official debut in a 4–1 win over [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]], coming on as a substitute and assisting [[Ousmane Dembélé]] and [[Bradley Barcola]]'s goals.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=16 August 2024 |title=PSG opens post-Mbappé era with 4-1 win at Le Havre in French league |url=https://www.newsday.com/sports/soccer/french-league-results-psg-s29370 |access-date=16 August 2024 |website=Newsday |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=16 August 2024 |title=João Neves makes debut |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/joao-neves-makes-debut-le-havre-ac-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-20242025 |access-date=17 August 2024 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]]}}</ref> On 23 August, he again provided two assists, one each for Barcola and [[Marco Asensio]], in a 6–0 victory over [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]]. In the process, he set the record for the most assists (four) in his first two Ligue 1 matches, surpassing [[Neymar]]'s previous record of three assists.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cassé |first=Josué |date=23 August 2024 |title=La statistique hallucinante de João Neves avec le PSG |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a7921561758202865030-la-statistique-hallucinante-de-joao-neves-avec-le-psg |access-date=26 August 2024 |website=Foot Mercato |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=23 August 2024 |title=João Neves Breaks Neymar Jr.'s Impressive Ligue 1 Record, Stat Reveals |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/jo-o-neves-breaks-neymar-223300418.html |access-date=7 September 2024 |website=Yahoo! Sports |language=en}}</ref> On 27 October, Neves scored his first goal for the club, netting the opening goal in a 3–0 win at away over [[Le Classique]] rivals [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=27 October 2024 |title=João Neves explica festejo após primeiro golo pelo PSG |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/joao-neves-explica-festejo-apos-primeiro-golo-pelo-psg-2024102722214534991 |access-date=28 October 2024 |website=[[A Bola]] |language=pt}}</ref>

On 22 January 2025, Neves was elected the player of the match in a 4–2 Champions League victory over [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 January 2025 |title=Portugal star Joao Neves admits "we shared many emotions" as Portuguese players light up Paris Saint-Germain's victory over Manchester City |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/portugal-star-joao-neves-admits-we-shared-many-emotions-as-portuguese-players-light-up-paris-saint-germains-victory-over-manchester-city-40601356 |access-date=23 January 2025 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> He won seven out of seven tackles, completed 51 out of 61 passes, and registered seven shots, eventually scoring the goal that completed PSG's comeback and put them up 3–2.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tharme |first=Liam |date=22 January 2025 |title=All-round brilliance from Joao Neves |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/psg-vs-manchester-city-live-updates-champions-league-score-result/m3oTAjcTJ9wH/akxAI0LToHEa/ |access-date=22 January 2025 |website=[[The Athletic]] |publisher=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> Having helped PSG secure their 13th Ligue 1 title, he was one of the nominees for the [[Ligue 1 Young Player of the Year]], finishing as runner-up and was included in the Ligue 1 Team of the Season, while also helping the club secure their first Champions League title and completing a [[Treble (association football)|continental treble]].<ref name=":5">{{Cite web |title=Ousmane Dembélé élu meilleur joueur de Ligue 1 pour la première fois aux Trophées UNFP |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Ousmane-dembele-elu-meilleur-joueur-de-ligue-1-pour-la-premiere-fois-aux-trophees-unfp/1561044 |access-date=11 May 2025 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0299-1de41a81a0d8-2cfefc69a802-1000--desire-doue-named-official-2025-uefa-champions-league-final/ |title=Désiré Doué named official 2025 UEFA Champions League final Player of the Match |publisher=UEFA |date=31 May 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=1 June 2025 |title='I have no words' - Champions League final MVP Desire Doue pays tribute to head coach Luis Enrique for trusting PSG star to step into Kylian Mbappe's shoes {{!}} Goal.com English Saudi Arabia |url=https://www.goal.com/en-sa/lists/i-have-no-words-champions-league-final-mvp-desire-doue-pays-tribute-to-head-coach-luis-enrique-for-trusting-psg-star-to-step-into-kylian-mbappe-s-shoes/blta19ecb4df34588aa |access-date=1 June 2025 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-SA}}</ref>

On 29 June, Neves scored his first career brace in a 4–0 win over [[Inter Miami]] in the round of 16 of the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]], becoming the first non-French player to score a brace for PSG in an international club competition match since [[Lionel Messi]] in October 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iffhs.com/posts/4462 |title=Club World Cup statistics (Round of 16, 29 June) |publisher=[[IFFHS]] |date=29 June 2025 |accessdate=2 July 2025}}</ref> On 13 July, in the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup final|final]] of the tournament, Neves was sent off for the first time in his career, for violent conduct, after pulling [[Marc Cucurella]]'s hair, in a match, where PSG were defeated 3–0 by [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.sky.com/story/chelsea-win-fifa-club-world-cup-with-victory-over-psg-as-donald-trump-watches-from-stands-13396284 |title=Chelsea win FIFA Club World Cup with victory over PSG - as Donald Trump presents trophy |publisher=Sky News |date=13 July 2025 }}</ref>

On 30 August, Neves scored his first career [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] in a 6–3 away win against [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]], including two bicycle kicks.<ref>{{Cite web |last=AFP |first=Paris |date=31 August 2025 |title=Joao Neves bags stunning hat-trick as PSG put six past Toulouse |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/sports/football/news/joao-neves-bags-stunning-hat-trick-psg-put-six-past-toulouse-3974781 |access-date=30 August 2025 |website=The Daily Star |language=en}}</ref> On 11 December, he made his 30th appearance in the UEFA Champions League in a 0–0 away draw to [[Athletic Bilbao]], becoming the youngest Portuguese player reach 30 appearances at the competition (21 years, and 14 days), breaking [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]'s record.<ref>https://www.abola.pt/noticias/joao-neves-bate-registo-de-cristiano-ronaldo-na-champions-2025121117392741584</ref> Neves was integral for the club and was a regular starter, as PSG secured their 12th league title in 14 years,<ref>{{Cite web |title=PSG's Dembele named UNFP Ligue 1 Player of the Year again |url=https://www.thescore.com/fra_fed/news/3539245 |access-date=2026-05-12 |website=thescore.com |language=en}}</ref> and on 30 May, they won their second consecutive UEFA Champions League title against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|final]] in a penalty shootout to retain the trophy.<ref>{{cite web |last=Howell |first=Alex |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj6ppx48pk2t |title=Paris Saint-Germain 1–1 Arsenal (4–3 on pens) |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Portugal national football team 0866 (João Neves).jpg|thumb|upright|Neves with [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in 2025]]

Neves represented [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at [[Portugal national under-15 football team|under-15]] and [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19]], for a total of 21 [[Cap (sport)|caps]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/Jogadores/Jogador/playerId/943216|title=João Neves|access-date=15 August 2022|website=Portuguese Football Federation|language=pt}}</ref> In June 2023, Neves took part in the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], scoring his first goal on 27 June in a 2–1 against [[Belgium national under-21 football team|Belgium]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2036139/ | title=History: Portugal 2-1 Belgium &#124; UEFA Under-21 2023 }}</ref> Portugal were eliminated from the tournament, on 2 July, after a 1–0 loss to [[England national under-21 football team|England]] in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66069220|title=England U21 1-0 Portugal U21|first=Alex|last=Howell|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=2 July 2023|access-date=14 July 2023}}</ref>

On 6 October 2023, Neves was called up to the [[Portugal national football team|Portuguese team]] for the first time for [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] matches against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]] and [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/41820|title=Roberto Martinez convoca para Eslováquia e Bósnia|website=[[Portuguese Football Federation]]|language=pt|date=6 October 2023}}</ref> He debuted the same year on 16 October, coming off the bench to replace [[Otávio (footballer, born 1995)|Otávio]] in the 85th minute of a 5–0 away victory against Bosnia and Herzegovina.<ref>{{Cite web|title=João Neves é o segundo estreante da "era" Roberto Martínez|trans-title=João Neves is the second debutant of the Roberto Martínez "era"|url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/selecao-nacional/joao-neves-e-o-segundo-estreante-da-era-roberto-martinez_d1521960|website=[[Rádio e Televisão de Portugal]]|date=16 October 2023|language=pt}}</ref>

On 21 May 2024, Neves was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Convocados para o Euro 2024|trans-title=Called up for Euro 2024|url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/news/45104|website=[[Portuguese Football Federation]]|date=21 May 2024|language=pt}}</ref> With Portugal having secured qualification from their group, he debuted in the competition as a starter in a 2–0 loss against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Ben|last=Fisher|title=Kvaratskhelia propels Georgia to last 16 with famous win over Portugal|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/jun/26/georgia-portugal-euro-2024-match-report|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=26 June 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036196--georgia-vs-portugal/ |title=Georgia 2–0 Portugal|website=[[UEFA]]|date=26 June 2024 }}</ref> Neves did not appear in the knockout stage as they were eliminated from the tournament in the quarter-finals after losing to [[France national football team|France]] 5–3 in a [[penalty shootout]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Emma|last=Sanders|title=Portugal 0–0 France (France win 5–3 on pens)|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy79llev4znt|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=5 July 2024|access-date=6 July 2024}}</ref>

On 20 May 2025, Neves was selected for Portugal’s [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals]] [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals squads#Portugal|squad]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Convocatória para Liga das Nações divulgada |trans-title=Nations League squad announced |url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-notícias/Notícia/news/50645 |website=[[Portuguese Football Federation]] |language=pt |access-date=26 May 2025 |date=20 May 2025}}</ref> Deployed as a right-back, he and his team would go on to win the tournament [[2025 UEFA Nations League final|5–3 in a penalty shootout]] over rivals [[Spain national football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6408339/2025/06/08/spain-portugal-yamal-mendes-ronaldo/|title=Spain 2 Portugal 2 (3–5 on pens): Mendes vs Yamal, Ronaldo being Ronaldo, and World Cup chances|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|first=Tim|last1=Spiers|first2=Dermot|last2=Corrigan|first3=Stu|last3=James|date=8 June 2025|access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref>

On 16 November, Neves scored his first senior international goals, netting in a hat-trick in a 9–1 victory over [[Armenia national football team|Armenia]] at [[Estádio do Dragão]], as Portugal secured qualification for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 November 2025 |title=João Neves e o hat trick pela Seleção: «Estou muito contente, mas o importante foi o apuramento» |trans-title=João Neves and the hat trick for the National Team: «I'm very happy, but the most important was qualifying» |url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/competicoes-de-selecoes/mundial/mundial-2026/detalhe/joao-neves-e-o-hat-trick-pela-selecao-estou-muito-contente-mas-o-importante-foi-o-apuramento |access-date=16 November 2025 |publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
[[File:DHS Secretary Kristi Noem Attends FIFA Club World Cup 2025 Championship Match - 54654518861.jpg|thumb|left|200px|João Neves tackling [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]'s [[Reece James]] during the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup final|FIFA Club World Cup final]].]]

Neves is a central midfielder known for his passing, tackling skills, and close ball control. Regarded for his composure, stamina, and tactical maturity and a young age,<ref>{{Cite web |title=João Félix: "O Neves tem 19 anos, mas parece que tem 30" |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/selecao/joao-felix/joao-felix-o-neves-tem-dezanove-anos-mas-parece-que-tem-trinta |access-date=13 November 2023 |website=Maisfutebol |language=pt}}</ref> he is capable of retaining possession under pressure in tight spaces. In addition, despite his relatively slight frame, statistics show that he wins a high percentile for aerial battles.<ref>{{Cite web |title=João Neves: Benfica's Homegrown Gem |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/joao-neves-benficas-homegrown-gem/ |access-date=13 November 2023 |website=Breaking The Lines |date=12 November 2023 |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Roseiro |first=Bruno |title=João Neves, um gigante dois em um que vê soluções e esconde problemas (a crónica do Benfica-Sporting) |url=https://observador.pt/2023/11/12/joao-neves-um-gigante-dois-em-um-que-ve-solucoes-e-esconde-problemas-a-cronica-do-benfica-sporting/ |access-date=13 November 2023 |website=Observador |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

At Benfica, Neves played as a [[deep-lying playmaker]], often in a double pivot within a [[4–2–3–1]] formation. In this role, he frequently dropped deep to receive the ball and keep possession. He uses his acceleration and agility over short distances to evade pressure from defenders and to create space from his marker without needing deceptive moves. Versatile in his positionings, Neves can drop between central defenders or full-backs to create numerical advantages. Defensively, he is noted for his counter-pressing, quickly engaging opponents to disrupt transitions when possession is lost.<ref>{{Cite web|title=João Neves position and style of play|url=https://www.coachesvoice.com/cv/joao-neves-position-and-style-of-play/|access-date=24 July 2024 |website=The Coaches Voice |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=JOÃO NEVES : THE ANATOMY OF A MIDFIELD DYNAMO.|url=https://mauteratti.medium.com/joao-neves-the-anatomy-of-a-midfield-dynamo-13bc1da3a4f8|access-date=24 July 2024 |website=Medium |date=25 March 2024 |language=en}}</ref>

